    {
      "content": "In what region should I locate my cache?",
      "pos": [
        3307,
        3347
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For best performance and lowest latency, locate your Azure Redis Cache in the same region as your cache client application.",
      "pos": [
        3349,
        3472
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How am I billed for Azure Redis Cache?",
      "pos": [
        3506,
        3544
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure Redis Cache pricing is <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>here<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/pricing/details/cache/)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3546,
        3633
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The pricing page lists pricing as an hourly rate.",
      "pos": [
        3634,
        3683
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Caches are billed on a per-minute basis from the time that the cache is created until the time that a cache is deleted.",
      "pos": [
        3684,
        3803
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There is no option for stopping or pausing the billing of a cache.",
      "pos": [
        3804,
        3870
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Why am I seeing timeouts?",
      "pos": [
        3905,
        3930
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Timeouts happen in the client that you use to talk to Redis.",
      "pos": [
        3932,
        3992
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For the most part Redis server does not time out.",
      "pos": [
        3993,
        4042
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When a command is sent to the Redis server, the command is queued up and Redis server eventually picks up the command and executes it.",
      "pos": [
        4043,
        4177
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However the client can time out during this process and if it does an exception is raised on the calling side.",
      "pos": [
        4178,
        4288
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information on troubleshooting timeout issues, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Investigating timeout exceptions in StackExchange.Redis for Azure Redis Cache<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/blog/2015/02/10/investigating-timeout-exceptions-in-stackexchange-redis-for-azure-redis-cache/)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4289,
        4552
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How do I monitor the health and performance of my cache?",
      "pos": [
        4586,
        4642
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Microsoft Azure Redis Cache instances can be monitored in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure preview portal<ept id=\"p1\">](https://portal.azure.com)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4644,
        4755
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can view metrics, pin metrics charts to the Startboard, customize the date and time range of monitoring charts, add and remove metrics from the charts, and set alerts when certain conditions are met.",
      "pos": [
        4756,
        4959
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These tools enable you to monitor the health of your Azure Redis Cache instances and help you manage your caching applications.",
      "pos": [
        4960,
        5087
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information on monitoring your caches, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Monitor Azure Redis Cache<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn763945.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        5088,
